rComments: she's a really nice prof, even if you stop her in the halls she's willing to answer questions. exam mc are almost all 2/3/all of the above options, which gets confusing but doable if you MEMORIZE the content. textbook was used to clarify images that we wanted us to know. very lecture based. go to office hours, she's really helpful

Rene Harrison is super passionate about cell bio and clear. Her lectures slides are fill in the blank so show up to class. Her exams are difficult but fair. Her MC is mostly choose the following from the following to answer questions 10-19. Her short answer qs are also very thought oriented like how would this error affect the whole system.

One of the best Profs at UTSC. She does an amazing job at introducing the core fundamentals of B level Biology. Quite approachable and extremely inspiring!! Her exams aren't too hard, but you need to study and look at the big picture. She does not use the text book, and sticks to that professional agreement. Awesome Prof!

Tbh she is a great prof when it come to teaching; however, her exams are pretty tough because of her formatting. Mainly all her questions consist of choosing "two of the above" or "all of the above" which trips with your mind. I would advise you to start studying ahead and make sure you go to her office hours because she's really helpful.

Good prof, but her tests are pretty hard. 70 percent of the questions were: a, b, c, two of the above, all of the above. This makes you second guess yourself a lot. Not cool. And considering it was only 40 percent midterm and 60 percent final, pretty hard to bring your mark up if you do bad on the midterm..

She will tell you exactly what she wants and exactly what she will test on. There were no surprises at all in the course. The assignments were doable but you definitely need to study further. The papers you get to study are almost always her papers or she somehow had an input into it so you are never lost and she WILL do her best to help you out!!

Professor Harrison is a great teacher! You do NOT need the textbook in this class as she'll only text you on things covered in lecture. Her midterm was easy but the final a bit harder. Make sure to write down everything she says in lecture!! I printed off her slides and made notes that way; just looking off slides isn't enough.
Best prof ever. She makes the exams simple and throws in a lot of give-away questions. I love her!
Her exams were fair and as a professor, she was very approachable and friendly.
Best bio prof I've ever had, explains material very well. Too bad I have Riggs this semester.  His lectures are extremely confusing and his lecture notes are made in 30s
Great professor!!!! :D
I love you<3 honestly best Prof at UTSC

one of the best profs ever.make sure you attend all her lectures and write down the extra notes which she only gives during lecture (they pop up in blue colour). Make sure you read the lecture notes and know your stuff really well...it's all about understanding the material...and yes, she's cute.

I liked her teaching style and she was always really clear. I really liked her. The class was 2 hours and had A LOT of information packed in, so sometimes it took a lot of concentration to keep focused. Her exams were fair but she likes to throw tricks in there, so make sure you read the questions really carefully.
She is an awesome teacher, too bad she's taking next year off (well not off, she said something about profs getting a year off every 7 years)...CANT WAIT TILL SHE COMES BACK!
Great prof. she has great lecture notes that coincide with the textbook..so u know exactly how to study for the exams..she keeps class interesting and doesn't mind answering numerous questions.
shes the best prof ever...im so in love with her!
Hi, Rene, you are such a great prof and scientist, and you've been a blessing and inspiration to my life.  Thank you so much!!! A++++++++++
Amazing professor!! I've come to love this class because of her. She puts so much effort into her students and actually makes the class interesting. Exams test knowledge but are fair. She's great!
great

Amazing Prof. So sweet and helpful not interested in hurting students. Really motivates one to learn and makes the material very interesting. Tricky exams know your stuff in and out. Not an EZ course but totally worth it. Thanks for making me feel like i actually learned something for once and did not just memorize and regurjitate for an exam!
She's so quarky/geeky it's hilarious. She's never hesistant to re-explain anything that seemed unclear. Uses very creative scenarios to demonstrate biological phenomena.

Hahaha the boys think she's hot, that's cute. I thought she was the funnest prof and actually made me enjoy learning the material. She is really sweet and approachable and really quirky and at times eccentric. Fun prof and you learn alot!

This prof is really intelligent! Her exam q's really test your knowledge, so whoever said this course is only about memorizing is very wrong! U better know your stuff well to the finest detail, otherwise the questions will confuse you! Very2 approachable and helpful. Try going to her office hour. You'll wish u can stay der d whole time to study.
This prof is super sweet and cool. I enjoyed all of her lectures and was sad to have finished the course. there was only one little problem, the final was brutal.

she's a great prof...knows her stuff like the back of her hand and loves to help students who don't understand the material. however, one thing...don't get mislead by seeing the lecture that they are easy!! THE EXAM IS VERY TRICKY AND HARD!!! YOU NEED TO UNDERSTAND AND MEMORIZE THE LECTURE NOTES. extra googling is also good for this course!! :)

O MY GOD!! She is so hot~ I hope I am not the only one that think shes hot!! I want her!! thats all i think bout in class~~tats why i cant pay attention in class..anyways back to the topic, the class material was loaded but she has a good way of explainin it..this class is all about memorizing
excellent prof overall

Professor Harrison is a really great prof - she makes her lectures very interesting with her energy and enthusiasm, and by throwing in little tidbits about her research and lab techniques and equipment. She is really nice, clear, considerate (as she asks the class if we want her to repeat something), and aware of what's happening in other classes.
Great Prof who really cares about her students.  Interesting researcher, and very easy on the eyes.
She's the most amazing prof/scientist to listen to.  Her course is hard, but so interesting. Highly recommended!
Great prof. unusally humble for a UofT prof. somehow managed to become a professor here without developing that condescending tone of arrogance everyone else has.

Her slides are very well prepared! Even as a new prof, she is one of the more interesting lecturers in the bio faculty. How many ppl can make cell bio funny? Also very approachable after class and very thorough in answering your questions. Fair exam that tested what was taught - no surprises.
That was a very enjoyable experience.  Thanks
One word sums her up: AMAZING! sure i could say more, she's funny, articulate, passionate about her work. when it boils down to it she's an amazing person and an amazing prof.  best class ever!
Overall good class, made the class fun by popping in her little jokes on the side, I thought those were hilarious.  Overall good class
Ecellent Prof!

LOVE this professor! she is absolutely THE best professor so far! makes university life a little easier with her easy to understand concepts on cell molec bio. I love her slides and jokes... i would love to be in her class again!
excellent professor! always able to help students out. makes the class fun and inetresting. her jokes are hilarious! very passionate about her research and enthusiastic! love her!

Wonderful Prof. Extremely nice and always cheerful. She loves when people come in for help and answers questions with a smiling face. She creates intimate bond with her students. Very enthusiatic prof.

New to the teaching circle. Most of the time she reads of her lecture notes, but tried to makes students occupied by leaving some parts of handouts blank. She knows her material thorugh and through. A very funny prof.
Excellent teacher.  Very enthusiastic.  She presents material in a clear and effective manner.  She is available for extra help whenever you need it and encourages people to come.

Professor Harrison is welcomed to questions from her students and helps them to grasp the concepts very well. Many hours are devoted to her students and is very sagacious in her studies.  She is an outstanding professor, I would have her again as my prof.
AWESOME, sweet and funny teacher. I really liked her. She presents the subject matter clearly and there's no reason why you shouldn't do well in her class. By the way, he name's pronounced "Reen"

She's soo articulate, funny and brand NEW! Although the course isn't easy, it is really not hard to comprehend if you study!!! I wish I could take the course again just to be taught by her again......she is an excellent Prof.
